@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Release Notes";
}
<p>What's new in the ePegboard web app at <a href="https://play.epegboard.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">play.epegboard.com</a>. The web app ships continuously - here are the highlights, most recent first.</p>

<h2 class="mt-5">Web app (play.epegboard.com)</h2>

<h3 class="mt-4 h4">June 2026</h3>
<ul class="fs-6">
    <li><strong>Better balanced games</strong> - the matchmaking has had a lot of work: more variety in who you play against, faster turnaround between games, and the option to show a live waiting queue like a traditional pegboard.</li>
    <li><strong>In-game substitutions</strong> - swap a player into a prepared game, or switch two players between teams, in a couple of taps.</li>
    <li><strong>Quicker score entry</strong> - the winning side is filled in for you at game over, the target score is shown, and the buttons are bigger for tablet touch.</li>
    <li><strong>Player profiles and history</strong> - every player gets a profile with their full session history (games won, rating changes, court time and wait time), and you can edit a player straight from their profile mid-session.</li>
    <li><strong>Clearer ratings for new players</strong> - a new player's fast-moving rating is marked as an estimate while it settles, and manual adjustments now show on the rating graph rather than appearing as an unexplained jump.</li>
    <li><strong>League team support</strong> - lock two players as a fixed pair within a normal session, and see a club-wide report of which partnerships work best.</li>
    <li><strong>Club insights</strong> - a redesigned reports hub: attendance trends, who is drifting away, member engagement, new-member conversion and game quality.</li>
    <li><strong>In-app news and session feedback</strong> - a news feed announcing new features, and an optional "how was tonight?" rating when you end a session.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="mt-4 h4">May 2026</h3>
<ul class="fs-6">
    <li><strong>Web app launched</strong> (10 May) - run a full club night in any browser on a tablet or laptop: check players in, auto-pick balanced games, enter scores and watch ratings update live. Existing clubs can import their Pegboard desktop history in one step.</li>
    <li><strong>Member management</strong> - bulk-import members from a spreadsheet, search and filter the member list, set membership types, and a new beginner rating tier.</li>
    <li><strong>Faster check-in</strong> - tap players in from a grid of photo tiles and add several at once, with an A-Z filter for larger clubs.</li>
    <li><strong>Richer stats</strong> - per-game rating changes on each player's list, sortable attendee tables, and a tidy layout on phones.</li>
    <li><strong>Built-in reports</strong> - session summary, payment summary, and a members CSV export.</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-5" />

<p class="text-muted">Looking for the Windows desktop app? Its version history has moved to the <a asp-page="/DesktopReleaseNotes">desktop app release notes</a>. The desktop app continues to be supported, but most new functionality is now going into the web app.</p>
